<p>
  Like a traditional webpage breadcrumb, the SERP breadcrumb provides a page's taxonomical
  context to the site's root. Each "crumb" is also a hyperlink to respective parent pages,
  providing the search result additional opportunities for organic traffic.
</p>

<p>
  Though Google also supports breadcrumbs in Microdata and RDFa formats, I'll use JSON-LD
  as per recommendation in their <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/structured-data/sd-policies#format">structured data general guidelines</a>. I also prefer
  JSON-LD for simplicity as it's an "under the hood" solution that doesn't rely on binding
  relational data with DOM structure.
</p>

